the i5 13600k provides the best performance in its price range

paired the i5 13600k with msi z690a pro ddr4 running pcores 54ghz and ecores 42ghz without any issues efficiency cores are powerful and theyre equivalent to i7 9700k from few years ago scores 25592 in cinebench 23 with all cores and 16507 with e cores disabled simply put amazing cant ask for more this cpu has no competition period

loving the price to performance with the 13600k considering i made the upgrade from a 6700k the technology is leaps and bounds for roughly same valuethere is also no reason to choose an amd5 cpu this year over the 13th gen intel chips maybe a x3d but definitely not the 7000 series of cpus

last home assembled pc lasted us about 12 years hopefully this newest setup will last 10 years too yes i spent a little more to have the newest but not the most powerful technology i have left room for upgrades in the future if i ever need to
